  "texts": [
    "In about half of them, the user study was the main contribution versus an add-on to evaluate a technical innovation (48.1% vs. 51.9%, respectively).",
    "Almost all user studies were experiments (95.6%), two were interviews (2.9%) and one was a work sample (1.5%).",
    "Most DNN models were based on some version of the ResNet architecture (42.6%), followed by VGG (20.6%) and Inception (13.2%).",
    "Furthermore, 13.2% of the studies relied on other models and 14.7% did not specify the model they used (see Figure 2D).",
    "In 23.5% of the studies, the model or dataset was intentionally manipulated to induce biases in the AI predictions or saliency maps."
